classified_errors.explanation: The tape manager (bptm) or disk manager (bpdm) received no data
raw_text: when it performed a backup, archive, or duplication. This error can occur for
incremental backups where no data was backed up because no files have changed.
Recommended Action: Do the following, as appropriate:
Check the All Log Entries report.

raw_text: its media catalog.
Recommended Action: Do the following, as appropriate:
Check the All Log Entries report for more information.

classified_errors.message: media manager detected image that was not in tar format
classified_errors.explanation: When you performed a restore, the tape manager (bptm) or disk
raw_text: manager (bpdm) did not find a tar header at the offset it expected.
Recommended Action: Do the following, as appropriate:
Perform a bpverify of the affected image to determine if it is written correctly.

classified_errors.explanation: When you load a volume for a backup or restore, the tape manager
raw_text: (bptm) found a volume that loaded without the expected tape header. This error
may mean that volumes in a robot are not in the slots that are indicated in the Media
and Device Management volume configuration.

classified_errors.explanation: The tape manager (bptm) searched for a backup image to restore
raw_text: but did not find the correct backup ID at the expected position on the volume. This
error can indicate a drive hardware problem.
Recommended Action: Do the following, as appropriate:
Try the restore on another drive if possible.

classified_errors.message: Media ID is not assigned to this host in the EMM database
classified_errors.explanation: An operation was requested on a media ID for which NetBackup
raw_text: does not have a record assigned to the requesting server. For example, you use
bpmedia to suspend or freeze a media ID that does not exist or is not assigned to
the requesting server.
NetBackup status codes

classified_errors.message: unable to allocate new media for backup, storage unit has none available
classified_errors.explanation: The NetBackup Resource Broker (nbrb) did not allocate a new volume
raw_text: for backups. This error indicates that the storage unit has no more volumes available
in the volume pool that is specified for this backup. Note that NetBackup does not
change storage units during the backup.
Recommended Action: Check the NetBackup Problems report to determine the
storage unit that is out of media.

classified_errors.message: requested media ID is in use, cannot process request
classified_errors.explanation: An operation was requested on a media ID that is in use. An example
raw_text: of this operation is the attempt to suspend or freeze a volume while it is in use for
a backup or restore.
Recommended Action: Retry the command when the volume is not in use. Use
the Device Monitor to determine if the volume is in use.

classified_errors.explanation: The paths in your NDMP policy file list did not back up successfully.
raw_text: One of the following occurred:
None of the backup paths exist on the NDMP host.
An NDMP backup uses a wildcard character that points to a file, not a file path.

raw_text: Recommended Action: Do the following, as appropriate:
Enable debug logging for bparchive, bpbackup, bplist, or bprestore (as
appropriate) by creating debug log directories for them.
